digital /ˈdɪdʒɪtəl/

1. ADJ Digital systems record or transmit information in the form of thousands of very small signals. 数码的 

例： The new digital technology would allow a rapid expansion in the number of TV channels. 新的数码技术可使电视频道的数量得以快速增多。 

2. ADJ Digital devices such as watches or clocks give information by displaying numbers rather than by having a pointer which moves round a dial. Compare . 数字的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...a digital display. …数字显示。 

3. PHRASE People sometimes refer to poorer people's lack of access to the latest computer technology as the digital divide . 数字鸿沟 [journalism] ['the/a' PHR] 

例： ...an attempt to reduce the 'digital divide' between poor students who have no computers and those from well-off families who do. …缩小没有电脑的贫困生和有电脑的富裕家庭学生之间的“数字鸿沟”的努力。

